-- Texas jury convicts woman of murder in so-called 'black widow' trial
-- 
-- Mon Sep 29, 2014 07:51PM EDT
-- None



Sept 29 (Reuters) - A Texas jury convicted a 45-year-old mother of four of murder and tampering with evidence on Monday in the 2011 shooting death of her husband in a suburb of Fort Worth in a plot to collect insurance money, an official said.

